listitem.simpara:
To access a table, you have to provide a specific Data Access Object which extends the Dao class, and add methods to retrieve or update your data. For exemple:
function & searchByID ($id) {
	$sql="SELECT * FROM log WHERE id='".$id."'";
	return $this->retrieve($sql);
}

In plugin constructor, add $id. Replace:
class <plugin_name>Plugin extends Plugin {
        function <plugin_name>Plugin() {
                $this->Plugin();
                ...
 by 
class <plugin_name>Plugin extends Plugin {
        function <plugin_name>Plugin($id) {
                $this->Plugin($id);
                ...

In plugin constructor, replace each occurence of
$this->hooks[] = "<name_of_hook>";
 by 
$this->_addHook("<name_of_hook>");

Change plugin_hook calls to event calls:
plugin_hook('the_corresponding_hook', $the_parameters);

becomes

$em =& EventManager::instance();
$em->processEvent('the_corresponding_hook', $the_parameters);
